[30;1m112 | [0m[35m<section id="smb2-support">[0m
[30;1m113 | [0m[35m<h2>SMB2 Support<a class="headerlink" href="#smb2-support" title="Permalink to this heading">¬∂</a></[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35m<p>Starting from pysmb 1.1.0, pysmb will utilize SMB2 protocol for communication if the remote SMB/C[0m
[30;1m115 | [0m[35mOtherwise, it will fallback automatically back to using SMB1 protocol.</p>[0m
[30;1m116 | [0m[35m<p>To disable SMB2 protocol in pysmb, set the <em>SUPPORT_SMB2</em> flag in the <em>smb_structs</em>[0m
